Feature: Request/Response Logging Middleware
  As an operations team member
  I want structured log entries for every request and response
  So that I can monitor API traffic with correlation tracing

  Background:
    Given the application is running with request logging enabled

  # ━━ GROUP A: Key Examples (4 scenarios) ━━

  # Why: Core — request received log contains required fields
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Request receipt is logged with required fields
    When I send a request to any endpoint
    Then a log entry with event "request.received" should be emitted
    And the log entry should contain the HTTP method
    And the log entry should contain the request path
    And the log entry should contain a correlation ID

  # Why: Core — response sent log contains required fields including duration
  @key-example @smoke
  Scenario: Response completion is logged with duration
    When I send a request to any endpoint
    Then a log entry with event "request.completed" should be emitted
    And the log entry should contain the status code
    And the log entry should contain a duration in milliseconds greater than zero
    And the log entry should contain a correlation ID

  # Why: Correlation ID matches across request and response log entries
  @key-example
  Scenario: Correlation ID is consistent across request and response logs
    When I send a request with correlation ID "log-trace-001"
    Then the "request.received" log entry should contain correlation ID "log-trace-001"
    And the "request.completed" log entry should contain correlation ID "log-trace-001"

  # Why: JSON format produces machine-parseable log output
  @key-example
  Scenario: Log output is valid JSON when JSON format is configured
    Given the application is configured with JSON log format
    When I send a request
    Then all log entries should be valid JSON

  # ━━ GROUP B: Boundary Conditions (3 scenarios) ━━

  # Why: Health check suppression — default behaviour avoids log noise
  @boundary
  Scenario: Health check paths are suppressed from logging by default
    Given the LOG_HEALTH_CHECKS setting is false
    When I request the liveness endpoint
    Then no "request.received" log entry should be emitted for that path

  # Why: Health check logging — can be enabled when needed
  @boundary
  Scenario: Health check paths are logged when the setting is enabled
    Given the LOG_HEALTH_CHECKS setting is true
    When I request the liveness endpoint
    Then a "request.received" log entry should be emitted for that path

  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Both /v1/health/live and /v1/health/ready are considered health check paths
  @boundary
  Scenario Outline: Both health endpoints are treated as health check paths
    Given the LOG_HEALTH_CHECKS setting is false
    When I request "<health_path>"
