    Examples:
      | health_path      |
      | /v1/health/live  |
      | /v1/health/ready |

  # ━━ GROUP C: Negative Cases (1 scenario) ━━

  # Why: Request log includes user_agent and content_length even when absent
  @negative
  Scenario: Missing optional fields are logged as null
    When I send a request without a User-Agent header
    Then the "request.received" log entry should contain user_agent as null

  # ━━ GROUP D: Edge Cases (3 scenarios) ━━

  # Why: Duration measurement is realistic — not zero, not absurd
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Duration is measured as wall clock time
    When I send a request to an endpoint
    Then the duration_ms in the response log should be greater than 0
    And the duration_ms should be less than 5000

  # Why: Response size is captured when available
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Response size is captured in the completion log
    When I send a request that returns a response body
    Then the "request.completed" log entry should contain response_size_bytes

  # Why: Concurrency — each concurrent request gets its own correlation ID in logs
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Concurrent requests each get independent correlation IDs in logs
    When I send 5 concurrent requests without correlation ID headers
    Then each "request.received" log entry should contain a unique correlation ID
    And each "request.completed" log entry should match its corresponding request correlation ID
